HEPATITIS G - BRAZIL (4)
========================
Dear Sir,
Hepatitis G virus has been identified from archival material
stored since 1978 (as presented in International Association for study of
Liver meeting at Cape Town 20-24 Feb 1996). It is a positive stranded RNA
virus and belong to Flavivirus group. As mentioned in Hepatitis G-Brazil
it is not a retrovirus. It is mostly transmitted by transfusion and often
associated with Hepatitis C virus and has chronic sequlae. PCR based
diagnostics are now available at laboratory level.
S K NANDA
Molecular Hepatitis LAB.
ALL INDIA INSTITUTE OF MEDICAL SCIENCES
NEW DELHI-110029
